        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Canton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-25T20:00:00-04:00">April 25, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. [For] Merchant. Dept concerned re possible large influx refugees. It is not
                    in position to judge whether it is feasible you discuss this <pb facs="0328" n="318" xml:id="pg_318"/> matter with Governor reminding him of his previous
                    stand to limit number of refugees to avoid further repercussions therefrom but
                    if so it is suggested you do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
